This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it deals with the task of detecting user intent in medical queries. It also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of a deep learning model and multi-task learning approach indicates that it could also be classified under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the focus on healthcare and medical information access strategies suggests that it could also be classified under the Cybersecurity (cs.CY) sub-category.
